casebody.data:
BANK OF TEHACHAPI v. CUMMINGS RANCH, Inc. No. 9409. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. May 8, 1940. Harvey, Johnston & Baker, of Bakersfield, Cal., for appellant. S. L. Kurland, of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellee.

Before WILBUR, MATHEWS, and STEPHENS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon consideration of record and briefs filed by respective parties, and oral argument had thereon, ordered order of District Court affirmed, without prejudice to right of appellant to make new application to trial court for such relief as it may desire; that a decree be filed and entered accordingly, and mandate issued in 30 days.
